## 🧪 Quality Gates (MUST PASS before committing)

### 1. Type Check
```
npx tsc --noEmit
```
❌ FAIL: Any TypeScript errors | ✅ PASS: Zero errors

### 2. Lint
```
npm run lint
```
❌ FAIL: Errors (warnings OK if documented) | ✅ PASS: Zero errors

### 3. Build
```
npx expo prebuild --clean
```
❌ FAIL: Build errors | ✅ PASS: Successful build for iOS & Android

### 4. Manual Test Checklist (per feature)
- [ ] Works on iOS simulator (iPhone 14)
- [ ] Works on Android emulator (Pixel 5)
- [ ] Dark mode renders correctly
- [ ] Loading states appear and resolve
- [ ] Error states show and allow retry
- [ ] Empty states display with CTAs
- [ ] Offline mode queues actions (if applicable)
- [ ] AI responses validated and handle failures gracefully
- [ ] No console warnings or errors in Metro bundler

---

## 🚫 Anti-Patterns (NEVER DO)

### Code Quality
- ❌ Using `any` type (use `unknown` and narrow, or define proper types)
- ❌ Ignoring TypeScript errors with `@ts-ignore` (fix the root cause)
- ❌ Hardcoding strings/numbers (extract to constants or design system)
- ❌ Copy-pasting code (extract to shared function/component)
- ❌ Nested ternaries >2 levels (extract to function or early returns)
- ❌ Large files >500 lines (split into smaller modules)

### React/React Native
- ❌ Inline styles (use Tailwind classes or design system)
- ❌ Missing keys in `.map()` (use stable IDs, not index)
- ❌ Side effects without cleanup (unsubscribe, cancel, clear timers)
- ❌ Missing error boundaries (wrap risky components)
- ❌ Prop drilling >3 levels (use context or state management)

### AI Integration
- ❌ Unvalidated AI responses (always use Zod or manual checks)
- ❌ Exposing raw AI errors to users (translate to friendly messages)
- ❌ Missing fallbacks (what if API is down? Use cached data or graceful degradation)
- ❌ Unbounded AI calls (rate limit per user)
- ❌ No token usage tracking (log every call for cost control)

### UX
- ❌ No loading states (user sees blank screen)
- ❌ No error feedback (user doesn't know what went wrong)
- ❌ No empty states (user sees confusing blank list)
- ❌ Tiny touch targets (frustrating on mobile)
- ❌ Blocking the UI (use background tasks for long operations)

---

## 📝 Naming Conventions

### Files & Folders
- Components: `PascalCase.tsx` (e.g., CalendarGrid.tsx)
- Utilities: `kebab-case.ts` (e.g., format-date.ts)
- Hooks: `use-camel-case.ts` (e.g., use-schedule.ts)
- Types: `kebab-case.types.ts` (e.g., schedule.types.ts)
- Feature folders: `kebab-case/` (e.g., ai-chat/, weekly-review/)

### Code
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., CalendarGrid, AIChat)
- Functions: camelCase (e.g., generateSchedule, parseNote)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., MAX_GOALS, AI_MODEL)
- Enums: PascalCase (e.g., SubscriptionTier, EventType)
- Interfaces/Types: PascalCase with I prefix optional (e.g., Schedule, IUser)

### Database (Supabase)
- Tables: snake_case, plural (e.g., users, schedules, notes)
- Columns: snake_case (e.g., user_id, created_at, goal_text)
- Indexes: idx_{table}_{columns} (e.g., idx_schedules_user_id)
- Functions: snake_case (e.g., get_user_schedules)

---

## 🔄 PDCA Integration

### When to Use Each Agent
- **pipeline-guide** → "What do I do first?", "Development order?"
- **pdca plan** → Start a new feature (creates docs/01-plan/features/{feature}.plan.md)
- **pdca design** → After plan, before coding (creates docs/02-design/features/{feature}.design.md)
- **pdca do** → Implement the feature per design
- **gap-detector** → Compare design vs implementation (creates docs/03-analysis/{feature}.analysis.md)
- **pdca-iterator** → Auto-fix gaps until match rate ≥90%
- **code-analyzer** → Code quality review (conventions, security, design match)
- **report-generator** → Completion report (creates docs/04-report/{feature}.report.md)

### Phase Handoff Rules
- **Plan → Design**: Plan MUST exist and define scope, user stories, success criteria
- **Design → Do**: Design MUST exist with API contracts, data models, components, error handling
- **Do → Check**: Implementation MUST be complete per design (all APIs, components, tests)
- **Check → Act**: Analysis MUST show match rate (target ≥90%) and list gaps
- **Act → Report**: Gaps fixed or documented as out-of-scope; ready for next cycle

---

## 🎯 Success Metrics (per Feature)

### Code Quality
- ✅ TypeScript strict mode, zero any
- ✅ ESLint pass (zero errors)
- ✅ Build success (iOS + Android)
- ✅ Match rate ≥90% (design vs implementation)

### UX Quality
- ✅ Loading states on all async actions
- ✅ Error states with retry
- ✅ Empty states with CTAs
- ✅ Touch targets ≥44×44dp
- ✅ Dark mode renders correctly

### AI Quality
- ✅ AI responses validated (Zod or manual)
- ✅ Fallback behavior on AI failure
- ✅ Rate limiting enforced
- ✅ Token usage logged

### Performance
- ✅ Screen transitions <300ms
- ✅ AI responses <5s (or show progress)
- ✅ Offline mode works (queue actions)

---

## 🚀 Deployment Checklist

### Pre-Deploy
- [ ] All PDCA phases complete (Plan → Design → Do → Check → Act → Report)
- [ ] Type check pass (npx tsc --noEmit)
- [ ] Lint pass (npm run lint)
- [ ] Build pass (npx expo prebuild --clean)
- [ ] Manual test on iOS + Android
- [ ] Dark mode tested
- [ ] Environment variables set in Vercel/Expo
- [ ] Supabase migrations applied (npx supabase db push)
- [ ] Rate limits configured
- [ ] Sentry/error tracking enabled

### Deploy
- [ ] Push to main branch
- [ ] Vercel auto-deploy (web) or EAS build (mobile)
- [ ] Smoke test production: auth, AI call, data sync
- [ ] Monitor logs for errors

### Post-Deploy
- [ ] Update docs/04-report/{feature}.report.md with deploy date
- [ ] Announce in Product Hunt / Reddit (if public launch)
- [ ] Monitor Sentry for errors
- [ ] Track KPIs: DAU, AI call success rate, error rate

