## 📚 Quick Reference

### Common Commands
```
# Dev
npm run start                   # Start Expo dev server
npm run ios                     # iOS simulator
npm run android                 # Android emulator

# Quality
npx tsc --noEmit                # Type check
npm run lint                    # Lint
npx expo prebuild --clean       # Clean build

# Supabase
npx supabase gen types typescript --project-id xxx > types/database.types.ts
npx supabase db push            # Apply migrations

# AI
# (No CLI; use lib/ai/ functions)
```

### Key Files
- Design tokens: `lib/design-system.ts`
- Supabase client: `lib/supabase/client.ts`
- AI wrappers: `lib/ai/schedule-generator.ts`, `lib/ai/note-parser.ts`
- Types: `types/database.types.ts`, `types/index.ts`

---

## 🆘 When Stuck
- **Design missing?** → Run `pdca design {feature}` or ask pipeline-guide
- **Code quality issues?** → Run code-analyzer
- **Implementation doesn't match design?** → Run gap-detector, then pdca-iterator
- **What's next?** → Run pdca status or pdca next
- **Need overall structure?** → Ask pipeline-guide "What are the 9 phases?"

---

Remember: Quality first. If something feels rushed or hacky, stop and refactor. Users can tell when a product cares about design and polish—that's our competitive edge.
